A transition that targets its own state in v5 is internal by default: neither exit nor entry actions run, and invoked actors stay alive. To force re-entry — useful when entry sets up a timer, restarts an invocation, or you want exit cleanup — set `reenter: true` on the transition. Transitions to a different state always cross state boundaries, so reentry doesn't apply there.

